cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DS, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method for multi-view clustering, which involves machine learning and data analysis. The paper specifically focuses on co-occurring data elements, which are commonly found in natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves clustering algorithms, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and experiments on image datasets, which are related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
